  "decision_conditions": [
    "Due to its inappropriate height dominating the main building, the proposed rear extension fails to maintain the scale and integrity, and fails to be subordinate to, the original building. The proposal also disrupts the harmony and consistency on rear of the terrace which exists above two storeys, harming the character and appearance of the host building, adjoining terrace and surrounding Duncan Terrace/Colebroke Row Conservation Area. The proposed works are, therefore, contrary to Policy 12 (Conserving and Enhancing the Historic Environment) of the National Planning Policy Framework 2012, and Policy CS9 (Protecting and Enhancing Islington’s Built and Historic Environment) of Islington’s Core Strategy (2011) and Policy DM2.3 of the Islington Development Management Policies (2013), the Duncan Terrace Colebrooke Row Conservation Area Design Guide and especially paragraph 3.20, and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006) and especially section 2.5.2."
